This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with optimizing relevance in search results. It may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it involves deriving mathematical relationships. Additionally, it could be classified under Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) as it pertains to search result diversification. The paper's focus on combinatorial optimization suggests it could also be categorized under Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
